<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=benemyjosh>Benemyjosh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/03 3:32:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2993.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What's the best way to train skills?</span><hr size=1> ok, that makes sense, but what if the skill is too low?  For example at level 20, my piercing and 2hb is only at 1.  Obviously I won't be able to do hardly any damage with those weapons.  I know with Piercing I could just put it in my off hand and that will make it go up, but with 2hb, I wouldn't be able to do much damage at all and that would mess up the group I'm in if i'm the main tank.  So how should I go about raising that skill?  Also any suggestions on what's the best way to increase my Bash skill would be great.  Right now my Bash is at 13 and I'l already level 20.<br>
<br>
Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=friedrick>Friedrick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/03 3:50:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2993.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What's the best way to train skills?</span><hr size=1> Here are some tips I will give you on training weapon skills.<br>
<br>
1.  Train 1 hand weapons first until double attack is maxed for level or 1 hand skills are maxed.<br>
<br>
2.  Get the fastest weapons you can find for a given skill (and don't go for big damage either, longer the mob is alive the more chances you have for skill ups)<br>
<br>
3.  Fight mobs that run and when a mob starts to run switch to a low skill weapon til it is dead, ie 2hb.<br>
<br>
4.  If you don't mind putting in a little time, find a full group of people and ask if they mind if you train your weapon skills on their mobs.  Their mob dies faster and you get weapon skill increases (but no exp).<br>
<br>
5.  In the 40's is a great time to catch up your neglected skills since you aren't increasing your skills til 50 again.<br>
<br>
6.  Not sure on Bash, I am a Barbarian and use slam or kick.  Honestly I am not sure I would worry too much about this skill.  Unless you have access to an amazing 1 handed weapon you probably won't use a shield anyway.  If you want to you could use tip 3 or 4 to accomplish this too I would think.<br>
<br>
Friedrick - 63rd Warlord on Tunare Server<br>
